value.title: Alphabet helps DeepMind to turn its first ever profit
value.excerpt: DeepMind, the London-based AI research firm, has turned a profit for the first time ever, reporting in £43.8 million in profits for 2020. The firm has posted multi-million-pound losses over the last several years and reportedly burned through $649 million in 2019.

value.title: European Parliament backs ban on remote biometric surveillance
value.excerpt: The European Parliament has voted to back a total ban on biometric mass surveillance. AI-powered remote surveillance technologies such as facial recognition have huge implications for fundamental rights and freedoms like privacy but are already creeping into use in public in Europe.

value.title: Singapore patrol robots warn people of ‘undesirable’ behavior
